This paper discusses techniques for improving the performance of neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The specific technique introduced in the paper, smart augmentation, involves generating augmented data to improve the generalization capability of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
